               <msContents>
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i1">
                     <rubric>Nomina sacra; name of the protagonist, names of the donor and his family members; groups of lines on the incipit page; incipit of all sections and subsections; elements of the punctuation signs and of the text dividers; elements of Ethiopic numerals.</rubric>
                     <incipit>
                        <foreign xml:lang="en"/>
                     </incipit>
                     <explicit>
                        <foreign xml:lang="en"/>
                     </explicit>
                     <note/>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem xml:id="coloph1">
                     <colophon>
                        <locus target="97va"/>Fol. 97va: ዝመጽሐፍ፡ የጌው[sic]፡ አቶ፡ ሀጐሥ፡ ዘአጽሐፎ፡ በንዋዩ፡ ዘወሀቦ፡ ለታቦተ፡ ቅዱስ፡ ጊዮርጊስ፡ ዘመአጐ፡ ከመ፡ ያድኅኖ፡ እመከራ፡ ሥጋ፡ ወነስፍ፡ ለፍቁሩ፡ ገብረ፡ ማርያ [fol. 97vb] ም፡ ወምስለ፡ ፍቅርቱ፡ ወለተ፡ ሥላሤ፡ ወምስለ፡ ደቂቁ፡... [fol. 98rb] ...ተጽሕፈ፡ በዘመነ፡ ሉቃስ፡ ወንጌላዊ፡ በዘመነ፡ መስፍንነ፡ ራስ፡ መንገሻ፡ ወገበዙ፡ መም[ሕ]ሬ፡ አብርሃ። በ፲፻በ፭፻ኮነ፡ ዓመተ፡ ዓለም። በ፲፻ወ፰፻ኮነ፡ ዓመተ፡ ምሕረት፡ የተጻፈበት፡ ወርቁ። ፮፡ የወንጌል፡ ፭ገበታ፡ የድ[ርሳነ]፡ ሚካኤል፡ ፰ብር፡ ፻ገበታ።<foreign xml:lang="en">Fol. 97va: This is the book of geta(?) ʾato Hagwäs who caused it to be written with his money and who donated it to the tabot of St. George of Mäʾagwä so that He might save his beloved Gäbrä Maryam [fol. 97vb] from the tribulations of the flesh and soul, together with his beloved Wälättä Śǝllase and with his children. ...
    [fol. 98rb] ... It was written in the year of Luke the Evangelist, during the time of our governor ras Mängäša (Yoḥannǝs) and qes gäbäz mämḥǝre ʾAbrǝha, in 1500 year of the world, in 1800 year of mercy. The money that the gospel has been written with is 6 (Bǝrr), 5 gäbätä (of grain) and the Homiliary for the feasts of St. Michael is 8 Bǝrr, 5 gäbätä (of grain).</foreign>
                        <note>The colophon is written in smaller script. The years mentioned in the colophon do not correspond with the mentioning of ras Mängäša (s. dating). The last part is written in Amharic.</note>
                     </colophon>
